# Sysmon Installation and Configuration on Windows

## Overview

Sysmon (System Monitor) is a Microsoft Sysinternals tool that logs detailed Windows system activity. It helps security professionals detect malicious behavior by recording process creation, network connections, file creation, registry modifications, and more.

---

## Prerequisites

- Windows 10/11 or Windows Server
- Administrator privileges
- Internet connection
- PowerShell or Command Prompt

---

## Step 1 – Download Sysmon

Download Sysmon from the Microsoft Sysinternals website.

https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/sysinternals/downloads/sysmon

Extract the ZIP file.

```
Sysmon.exe
Sysmon64.exe
Eula.txt
```

---

## Step 2 – Download the Configuration File

Download the SwiftOnSecurity Sysmon configuration.

https://github.com/SwiftOnSecurity/sysmon-config

Save the file as:

```
C:\Tools\Sysmon\sysmonconfig-export.xml
```

---

## Step 3 – Create the Working Folder

```cmd
mkdir C:\Tools\Sysmon
```

Copy the following files into the folder:

```
Sysmon64.exe
Sysmon.exe
sysmonconfig-export.xml
```

---

## Step 4 – Open Command Prompt as Administrator

Search for **Command Prompt**, right-click it, and select **Run as Administrator**.

---

## Step 5 – Navigate to the Folder

```cmd
cd C:\Tools\Sysmon
```

Verify the files:

```cmd
dir
```

---

## Step 6 – Install Sysmon

```cmd
Sysmon64.exe -accepteula -i sysmonconfig-export.xml
```

---

## Step 7 – Verify the Installation

Command Prompt:

```cmd
sc query Sysmon
```

PowerShell:

```powershell
Get-Service Sysmon
```

The service status should be **Running**.

---

## Step 8 – Open Event Viewer

Navigate to:

```
Applications and Services Logs
 └── Microsoft
      └── Windows
           └── Sysmon
                └── Operational
```

---

## Step 9 – Generate Test Events

```cmd
ipconfig

whoami

ping google.com

notepad.exe
```

---

## Step 10 – Verify Events

You should observe:

| Event ID | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| 1 | Process Creation |
| 3 | Network Connection |
| 11 | File Creation |
| 13 | Registry Modification |
| 22 | DNS Query |

---

## Step 11 – View the Current Configuration

```cmd
Sysmon64.exe -c
```

---

## Step 12 – Update the Configuration

```cmd
Sysmon64.exe -c sysmonconfig-export.xml
```

---

## Step 13 – View Recent Logs

```powershell
Get-WinEvent -LogName "Microsoft-Windows-Sysmon/Operational" -MaxEvents 20
```

---

## Step 14 – Uninstall Sysmon

```cmd
Sysmon64.exe -u
```

---

## Useful Commands

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Sysmon64.exe -i config.xml | Install Sysmon |
| Sysmon64.exe -c config.xml | Update configuration |
| Sysmon64.exe -c | View configuration |
| Sysmon64.exe -u | Uninstall Sysmon |
| sc query Sysmon | Check service |
| Get-Service Sysmon | Verify service |
| Get-WinEvent | View Sysmon logs |

